International:
   Japan Telecom Joint Venture
Tentatively called Tokai Digital Phone, the new company
will be based in Nagoya City, with capital of three billion
yen ($24 million). Services are expected to be available in
1994.
   Japan Telecom intends to take up 29.5% of the capital,
while Pacific Telesis will contribute 13%. Japanese passenger
railway company Tokai Ryokaku Tetsudo K.K. is expected to
take 12%; Cable  Wireless PLC of Britain, 7.2%; Toyota Motor
Corp.; 4%; and CSK Corp. of Japan, 4%.
   Among about 20 other companies expected to participate are
KDD of Japan, an international telecommunications company;
Yamaha Motor Co.; Nippon Steel Corp.; and Suzuki Motor Corp.